WEBVTT

00:01.169 --> 00:03.737
You know the kind of guy
who does nothing
but bad things...

00:03.771 --> 00:07.341
and then wonders why
his life sucks?

00:07.375 --> 00:11.112
Well, that was me.
Every time somethin' good
happened to me,

00:11.145 --> 00:13.247
somethin' bad
was always waitin'
around the corner.

00:15.449 --> 00:17.051
Karma.

00:17.085 --> 00:19.187
That's when I realized
I had to change.

00:20.721 --> 00:23.391
So I made a list
of everything bad
I've ever done,

00:23.424 --> 00:26.360
and, one by one,
I'm gonna make up
for all my mistakes.

00:26.394 --> 00:28.329
I'm just tryin'
to be a better person.

00:28.362 --> 00:30.631
My name is Earl.

00:32.266 --> 00:34.535
[ Chattering ]

00:34.568 --> 00:36.837
All right, everybody.

00:36.870 --> 00:39.107
The competition starts
in two minutes. Two minutes.

00:39.140 --> 00:41.309
Get your spot.

00:41.342 --> 00:46.180
You know the rules.
Competitor puts their hand
on the car.

00:46.214 --> 00:50.118
If at any point in time
they take their hand
off the car, they're out.

00:51.652 --> 00:54.688
You can't come between us.
We're Chinese twins.
Yeah.

00:54.722 --> 00:57.425
[ Earl Narrating ]
So why am I trying
to win a car...

00:57.458 --> 01:00.394
when I already have a perfectly
good 1973 El Camino...

01:00.428 --> 01:04.232
with a 1977 door
and a 1987 Camaro transmission?

01:04.265 --> 01:07.601
Well, it's not for me.
It's for the list.

01:07.635 --> 01:09.503
Number 74-- always ruined
Joy's Christmas.

01:11.605 --> 01:15.509
When Joy and I were married,
I wasn't exactly thoughtful
with my gift-givin'.

01:18.746 --> 01:21.449
What are these for?
Whatever you want, baby.

01:31.459 --> 01:34.862
- How are these for me?
- They're flavored.
Merry Christmas.

01:39.667 --> 01:41.702
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

01:44.272 --> 01:46.440
- Wait. These are my keys.
- I know. I found 'em.

01:53.914 --> 01:57.151
Do we have to give
this car to Joy
if we win?

01:57.185 --> 02:01.322
We could use a new car
ourselves. You know,
one to do stunts with.

02:01.355 --> 02:04.325
Randy, I didn't give her
a real Christmas gift
for six years.

02:04.358 --> 02:07.428
- I gotta give her something big
to make up for that.
- But she already has a car.

02:07.461 --> 02:10.498
Excuse me, ma'am.
Thank you.

02:10.531 --> 02:13.834
[ Thunder Rumbling ]
[ Earl Narrating ]
Joy did already have a car.

02:13.867 --> 02:16.470
Wipe your feet
before you come in, boys.

02:16.504 --> 02:20.208
But it wasn't very practical
for the whole family.

02:20.241 --> 02:23.611
All right, one minute.
One minute till
the competition begins.

02:23.644 --> 02:25.679
Earl.

02:25.713 --> 02:28.282
- Randy.
- Catalina,
where have you been?

02:28.316 --> 02:32.253
I had... to blow...

02:32.286 --> 02:34.188
off work.

02:34.222 --> 02:37.325
Well, hurry in here.
This thing's about to start.

02:37.358 --> 02:39.227
[ Catalina ]
Excuse me. Excuse me.
Permiso.

02:39.260 --> 02:41.195
[ Man ]
We were here first.
[ Woman ] Yeah.

02:41.229 --> 02:42.830
I'm on.

02:42.863 --> 02:47.401
I'm Johnny Bubble Wrap,
pop, pop, pop, poppin'
with ya live...

02:47.435 --> 02:49.537
at our hands on a car
competition.

02:49.570 --> 02:52.806
- Who wants to win a car?
- [ Cheering ]

02:54.842 --> 02:58.579
All right, everybody.
Hands on the car.

02:58.612 --> 03:01.682
Three, two, one.

03:01.715 --> 03:03.784
Don't let go.

03:03.817 --> 03:05.853
Thanks for doing this
with me, Randy.

03:05.886 --> 03:08.689
If we work together as a team,
keep an eye on each other,

03:08.722 --> 03:10.991
make sure we stay alert,
I think we can win this.

03:11.024 --> 03:13.227
Let's do it.
Yep.

03:13.261 --> 03:14.995
[ Buzzer ]
You're out!

03:15.028 --> 03:18.566
No, no, no.
I was just shakin'
his hand.

03:18.599 --> 03:21.802
- I didn't mean to.
- Oh. You're out!

03:21.835 --> 03:24.338
Yeah. You're out, buddy.

03:24.372 --> 03:26.540
You are out.
[ Laughs ]
[ Buzzer ]

03:28.709 --> 03:31.579
Damn it.

03:31.612 --> 03:33.714
This sucks.
What am I gonna do now?

03:33.747 --> 03:37.618
Don't worry, Earl.
Me and Catalina are here.
We're gonna win.

03:37.651 --> 03:40.254
- [ Man Grunts ]
- Thanks, Randy.

03:40.288 --> 03:41.955
Keep your hand
on the roof.

03:45.793 --> 03:48.662
[ Earl Narrating ]
While Randy was keeping
his hand on the car for me,

03:48.696 --> 03:51.499
I thought I'd take care
of another thing on my list.

03:51.532 --> 03:56.304
You see, Joy wasn't the only
person I disappointed when it
came to Christmas presents.

03:56.337 --> 04:00.341
[ Both Chuckling ]

04:00.374 --> 04:02.843
- Earl, did you finish putting
the boys' bikes together?
- Uh-huh.

04:02.876 --> 04:05.913
There better be
some of that beer left
for Christmas mornin'.

04:05.946 --> 04:09.350
We should go on a beer run.
Are we okay to drive?

04:09.383 --> 04:11.885
I know a good way
to find out.

04:11.919 --> 04:15.589
If I can steer that
remote control car around the
living room without crashing,

04:15.623 --> 04:17.758
then we're okay.

04:17.791 --> 04:19.593
Randy, that's the cat.

04:21.595 --> 04:24.031
- [ Meows ]
- We shouldn't drive.

04:24.064 --> 04:26.600
[ Chuckles ]

04:26.634 --> 04:29.303
That's when I realized
we might be too drunk
to drive,

04:29.337 --> 04:31.439
but we weren't
too drunk to pedal.

04:31.472 --> 04:33.574
Although I learned
a valuable lesson that night.

04:33.607 --> 04:35.743
If you're gonna try
to fly a bicycle,

04:35.776 --> 04:39.012
you better make sure
E.T. is sitting in your basket
instead of a 12-pack of beer.

04:39.046 --> 04:40.581
[ Bike Horn Honks ]
[ Crash ]

04:40.614 --> 04:42.650
[ Distorted Horn Honks ]

04:46.820 --> 04:49.657
Well, I guess you two
weren't good enough
this year, huh?

04:49.690 --> 04:51.825
That's a shame.

04:51.859 --> 04:53.827
[ Bicycle Bell Rings ]
[ Distorted Horn Honks ]

04:53.861 --> 04:56.564
Knowin' I owed these poor kids
a couple of bikes,

04:56.597 --> 04:59.533
I went over to ask Joy
what color they might like.

04:59.567 --> 05:01.935
Hello?
Earl!

05:01.969 --> 05:04.938
Son of a bitch.
[ Laughs ]

05:04.972 --> 05:07.408
Buzz and Connie Darville.
Joy's parents.

05:07.441 --> 05:09.610
Good people.
Business owners.

05:09.643 --> 05:13.080
Hi. We're the Darvilles.
Of Darville's Waterbeds
in Medford.

05:13.113 --> 05:16.116
If you can find a cheaper
place in Medford to
buy a water bed,

05:16.149 --> 05:19.019
well, you're not in Medford,
because we're the only
water bed store.

05:19.052 --> 05:21.922
So come on down
if you wanna sleep on water.

05:21.955 --> 05:23.924
[ Together ]
You don't have any other choice.

05:23.957 --> 05:25.926
[ Announcer ]
Darville Waterbeds,

05:25.959 --> 05:27.995
where Route 2
meets the railroad tracks.

05:28.028 --> 05:31.131
Look for the big blue sign,
go two miles south, make a left,

05:31.164 --> 05:33.367
and park behind the Dumpster.

05:33.401 --> 05:35.369
- Buzz, Connie.
- You're back.

05:35.403 --> 05:38.606
- I'm what?
- Welcome home, soldier.

05:38.639 --> 05:40.374
[ Joy ]
You're back.

05:40.408 --> 05:42.976
Oh, my God! You're back.
[ Chuckles ]

05:43.010 --> 05:45.646
You're back from Iraq,
home for the holidays.

05:45.679 --> 05:47.781
Back from the war in Iraq.

05:54.722 --> 05:57.525
I prayed you'd
come home safely, Son.

05:57.558 --> 06:00.160
You bring any of that
Middle East sand
with you?

06:00.193 --> 06:03.464
Check your shoes, Son.
'Cause you can sell that stuff
on the Internet.

06:03.497 --> 06:06.166
I bought a towel
from one of Saddam's
bathrooms.

06:06.199 --> 06:10.103
Had a dove on it.
You believe that?
A dove.

06:10.137 --> 06:12.706
- That hypocritical
son of a bitch.
- Son of a bitch.

06:12.740 --> 06:15.175
[ Chuckles ]
Mama, Daddy,

06:15.208 --> 06:18.479
he's been gone for months,
and a wife has her needs,

06:18.512 --> 06:20.581
so if y'all
will excuse us.

06:20.614 --> 06:23.484
- Take me to the bedroom.
- What?

06:23.517 --> 06:25.385
Take me to the bedroom.

06:28.522 --> 06:30.791
- Go on, Son.
You-- You've earned it.
- Thanks.

06:34.862 --> 06:37.765
What the hell is goin' on?
Why are your parents
still callin' me "Son"?

06:37.798 --> 06:40.100
- They think
we're still married.
- What?

06:40.133 --> 06:41.969
Shh.

06:42.002 --> 06:44.171
You know how traditional
my parents are.

06:44.204 --> 06:48.075
If they found out I got divorced
and married to a black man,
they'd crap in a sock.

06:48.108 --> 06:50.678
They think of me as their
little angel. Now come on.

06:50.711 --> 06:54.515
Help me slosh around
on the water bed and make it
sound like we're doin' it.

06:54.548 --> 06:56.517
[ Earl Narrating ]
This isn't the first time...

06:56.550 --> 06:58.752
Joy's asked me to lie
to her parents about Darnell.

06:58.786 --> 07:02.022
She'd made me do it
when we were married
and she had his baby.

07:02.055 --> 07:05.058
You know how, uh, sometimes
two, uh, black people...

07:05.092 --> 07:07.695
will make an albino baby?

07:07.728 --> 07:12.566
Yeah. I've seen that
at the mall.
That is weird.

07:12.600 --> 07:15.536
You been away too long.
Too long.

07:15.569 --> 07:18.071
Wait. Why is your mother
in a wheelchair?

07:18.105 --> 07:21.041
It's been a rough year.
She got rheumatoid arthritis
and kidney failure.

07:21.074 --> 07:23.877
Has to get dialysis
twice a week, poor thing.

07:23.911 --> 07:27.147
[ Water Sloshing ]
Oh, yeah.
Give it to me, Earl.

07:27.180 --> 07:30.584
Give it to me like you
gave it to those terrorists.
Oh, yeah.

07:30.618 --> 07:33.987
Wouldn't mind you
being that passionate
sometimes.

07:34.021 --> 07:36.056
Her legs work.

07:38.892 --> 07:41.495
I'm not gonna do this,
Joy. I got my list now.

07:41.529 --> 07:43.564
I'm trying to be
a better person.

07:43.597 --> 07:46.199
I'm not gonna
lie to a woman
in a wheelchair.

07:46.233 --> 07:49.970
Earl, if Daddy finds out
about Darnell, I won't
get a penny in his will.

07:50.003 --> 07:53.006
He found out I was gonna
go on a date with a black guy
in high school,

07:53.040 --> 07:55.809
and he threatened
to take away
all my white blue jeans.

07:55.843 --> 07:58.712
Darnell's okay with this?
He doesn't care that his
wife's father is a racist?

07:58.746 --> 08:02.716
Darnell is fine with it.
Not everybody is tryin'
to change the world, Earl.

08:02.750 --> 08:05.786
Some of us are just trying
to get our fair taste
of a water bed business...

08:05.819 --> 08:07.955
when our parents
kick the bucket.

08:07.988 --> 08:10.290
[ Earl Narrating ]
Turns out Darnell
was fine with it.

08:10.323 --> 08:13.527
While Joy's parents
were in town, he was staying
at a nativity scene...

08:13.561 --> 08:18.231
down at the local church
since there wasn't room for him
at his own double-wide inn.

08:18.265 --> 08:22.035
- I can't lie to 'em, Joy.
It's bad karma.
- Karma this, dummy.

08:22.069 --> 08:26.574
If you tell them the truth,
they'll both get in their R.V.
and drive home.

08:26.607 --> 08:30.177
- That's not my problem.
- You're gonna ruin
Christmas, Earl.

08:30.210 --> 08:32.245
[ Earl Narrating ]
She had me.

08:32.279 --> 08:35.749
The last thing I wanted to do
was ruin Christmas.

08:35.783 --> 08:39.252
So the next few days,
I pretended Joy and I
were still married.

08:45.058 --> 08:48.228
What's it like
fightin' over there
in the desert?

08:50.163 --> 08:53.000
Well, Buzz,
it's a lot like the beach.

08:53.033 --> 08:57.070
Except the sharks have guns,
and they're runnin' around
on the sand shootin' at ya...

08:57.104 --> 08:59.239
and yellin' in a fish language
you don't understand.

08:59.272 --> 09:01.141
It-- It got to me.

09:03.010 --> 09:05.078
He's my hero.

09:05.112 --> 09:08.148
Oh, honey.
Yes, he is.

09:08.181 --> 09:10.183
[ Earl Narrating ]
I'd take the day shift,

09:10.217 --> 09:13.353
and Darnell would sneak back in
for the night shift.

09:13.386 --> 09:18.225
Thanks, Earl. It's cold
outside in that manger.
I don't know how Jesus did it.

09:18.258 --> 09:21.662
No problem, Crab Man.
I'll be back in the morning.

09:21.695 --> 09:24.932
- Put a beer can in the window
when it's safe to come in.
- Okay.

09:24.965 --> 09:28.035
[ Earl Narrating ]
While I was busy making sure
I didn't ruin Joy's Christmas,

09:28.068 --> 09:30.103
Randy was keeping his hand
on that car...

09:30.137 --> 09:33.040
so I could cross her off
for ruinin' the last six.

09:38.178 --> 09:41.348
[ Earl Narrating ]
After a few days,
time took its toll,

09:41.381 --> 09:44.117
and there were only
three people left-- and one
of them was gettin' tired.

09:45.318 --> 09:47.320
[ Mouthing Words ]

09:49.322 --> 09:52.025
[ Screaming ]
[ Buzzer ]

09:52.059 --> 09:54.895
- You're out.
- Damn it.

09:54.928 --> 09:58.098
We did it, Catalina.
We won. Joy's gonna
get her car.

09:58.131 --> 10:01.401
Joy? I'm not
doing this for Joy.
I hate Joy.

10:01.434 --> 10:05.806
B-But I-- I thought we were
doing this together.
You know, like a team.

10:05.839 --> 10:09.376
I never said that.
When I win this car,
I'm keeping it.

10:09.409 --> 10:11.912
But Catalina,
winning this car for Joy...

10:11.945 --> 10:13.914
is my Christmas present
to Earl.

10:13.947 --> 10:16.784
This is for a family
at Christmas.

10:16.817 --> 10:21.354
- You know,
feliz "naviblah."
- That means nothing.

10:21.388 --> 10:25.092
To you, maybe,
but in American that means
Christmas in Mexican.

10:27.060 --> 10:29.897
Joy and her dad had taken
the boys to the mall,

10:29.930 --> 10:32.766
so it was the perfect time
to sneak their new bikes
into the trailer.

10:32.800 --> 10:36.236
Joy's mom was home,
but I was confident
she could keep a secret.

10:36.269 --> 10:38.171
[ Connie ]
Go, go, go!
Yes, go, yes, go!

10:38.205 --> 10:41.308
Oh, yes, yes, yes, yes!

10:41.341 --> 10:43.711
Go, go, go, go!

10:43.744 --> 10:47.347
Atta baby! Go, baby!
Go, baby, go, baby!
Go, go, go, go.

10:47.380 --> 10:49.382
Oh, damn-- it.

10:49.416 --> 10:52.152
Hey.

10:52.185 --> 10:54.421
Turns out Connie
had a secret of her own.

11:00.828 --> 11:03.363
- You can walk.
- Oh, my God.

11:03.396 --> 11:06.900
- Is that what I'm doing?
- Were you gambling?

11:06.934 --> 11:11.071
Fine. Damn it.
I've got a gambling problem,
okay?

11:11.104 --> 11:13.974
Not all of us can be lucky
enough to get our thrills...

11:14.007 --> 11:16.309
from going off
and killing bad people.

11:16.343 --> 11:20.714
- Don't you judge me.
- No, I-I'm not judging you. I--

11:20.748 --> 11:23.817
I'm just a little
surprised, that's all.
So you're not sick?

11:23.851 --> 11:26.286
I fake dialysis
so Buzz doesn't know
I go to the track.

11:26.319 --> 11:30.123
He thinks we get
a 10% discount if I
pay the doctor in cash.

11:33.393 --> 11:36.296
Buzz, give me
a thousand dollars.
I gotta go in for dialysis.

11:36.329 --> 11:39.099
Again? You just went
this morning.
Yeah.

11:39.132 --> 11:41.401
My kidney's
really flarin' up today.

11:41.434 --> 11:43.370
Let me take you.
Just give me the grand.

11:43.403 --> 11:45.505
Post time's in 20 minutes.
Post time?

11:45.538 --> 11:48.275
I don't have time
to explain medical terms
to you.

11:48.308 --> 11:50.510
My kidney's failin'.

11:50.543 --> 11:54.114
I understand the kidney stuff
to explain the money
and the time to go gamble.

11:54.147 --> 11:57.851
But why the wheelchair?
Seems unnecessary.

11:57.885 --> 12:00.854
I sprained my ankle a few
months ago, and I got used
to being pushed around.

12:00.888 --> 12:02.990
- Don't you judge me.
- No, I'm not--

12:03.023 --> 12:06.760
- [ Car Horn Honks ]
- [ Connie ]
Oh, my God. Is that them?

12:06.794 --> 12:09.229
Oh, my God.
Earl, please don't tell.
They're gonna be so mad.

12:09.262 --> 12:11.999
You're not gonna
let 'em know, are you?
It'll ruin Christmas.

12:12.032 --> 12:15.068
You don't want to ruin
Christmas, do you, Earl?

12:15.102 --> 12:17.838
[ Earl Narrating ]
The last thing I wanted to do
was ruin Christmas.

12:20.540 --> 12:23.210
- [ Gasps ]
- [ Earl Groans ]

12:23.243 --> 12:27.180
Her favorite song
came on the radio, and she
really wanted to dance.

12:27.214 --> 12:30.150
[ Snapping Fingers ]

12:30.183 --> 12:33.153
While I was busy
keeping everyone's secrets,

12:33.186 --> 12:37.057
Randy and Catalina
were battling it out
for the car.

12:37.090 --> 12:40.293
For a woman who spent
four days on a raft
to get to America,

12:40.327 --> 12:43.563
Catalina was surprisingly
sensitive to the sun.

12:43.596 --> 12:46.333
Catalina?

12:46.366 --> 12:48.435
Catalina?
Papa?

12:48.468 --> 12:50.437
No, Catalina.
It's me, your friend Randy.

12:50.470 --> 12:53.841
I don't know where
the goat went, Papa.

12:56.977 --> 12:59.079
You bastard.
When a woman faints,
you catch her.

12:59.112 --> 13:02.182
When a woman faints,
she doesn't keep
her hand on the car.

13:02.215 --> 13:05.252
Damn. My elbow's bleeding.
I hit a rock.

13:05.285 --> 13:07.855
And this is
my favorite elbow.

13:07.888 --> 13:10.157
Don't show me blood.
I-- I can't see blood.

13:10.190 --> 13:13.160
Why? Do you have
a problem with blood?

13:13.193 --> 13:15.295
[ Groans ]

13:15.328 --> 13:17.330
- [ Buzzer ]
- You're out!

13:17.364 --> 13:19.299
We got a winner.

13:23.971 --> 13:27.975
Well, congratulations.
We have a lot of paperwork
to fill out.

13:28.008 --> 13:30.577
You wanna start
by giving me your
Social Security number?

13:30.610 --> 13:33.180
My what?

13:33.213 --> 13:35.849
Your Social
Security number.

13:35.883 --> 13:37.584
Of course.

13:37.617 --> 13:40.020
4-2...

13:40.053 --> 13:43.356
1-3-6-7-8...

13:43.390 --> 13:46.493
2-5-7-6...

13:46.526 --> 13:52.132
8-14-11-6.

13:52.165 --> 13:54.902
Six. You a citizen?

14:03.043 --> 14:06.479
[ Earl Narrating ]
Turns out Catalina
had a secret of her own.

14:19.292 --> 14:21.528
Randy won the car
by default.

14:21.561 --> 14:24.097
Everything was fallin'
into place.

15:30.630 --> 15:31.698
[ Gasps ]

15:33.333 --> 15:36.069
Hey--

15:36.103 --> 15:39.339
Hey, Connie.
Where are you goin'?

15:39.372 --> 15:42.575
To the Indian casino.
I have to gamble, Earl.
I have a problem.

15:42.609 --> 15:44.611
Don't judge me.
What--

15:44.644 --> 15:46.479
But that's Joy's
Christmas gift.

15:52.485 --> 15:55.655
[ Starter Cranking ]

16:19.412 --> 16:21.581
Where's the car?

16:23.116 --> 16:26.053
At the Indian casino.
I lost it.

16:26.086 --> 16:28.688
How could you lose
the car?

16:28.721 --> 16:30.523
Place your bets.
Place your bets.

16:35.195 --> 16:37.497
Dodge Neon on number seven.

16:37.530 --> 16:40.267
Dodge Neon.

16:40.300 --> 16:43.370
- Dodge Neon plays.
- Yes.

16:45.672 --> 16:48.441
I can't believe
you lost my car.
That car was for Joy.

16:48.475 --> 16:52.179
- I was gonna give it
to her for Christmas.
- Don't you judge me.

16:57.217 --> 17:00.053
Come on.
It's been 20 minutes.
It's my turn.

17:00.087 --> 17:02.722
No, it hasn't.
I been counting.
You said we'd share.

17:06.559 --> 17:09.496
Maybe you can go out
to the dealership
in the morning...

17:09.529 --> 17:11.598
and get a new one,
you know?

17:11.631 --> 17:14.401
I think they give
discounts to soldiers.

17:14.434 --> 17:16.503
Connie?
You're walkin'.

17:18.605 --> 17:20.607
It's a Christmas miracle.

17:20.640 --> 17:22.242
[ Door Opens ]

17:23.610 --> 17:26.379
Mama, where's
your wheelchair?

17:26.413 --> 17:28.648
Connie,
what's goin' on?

17:28.681 --> 17:31.384
I'm done, Connie.

17:32.752 --> 17:35.788
Oh. Okay. I have
a gambling problem.

17:35.822 --> 17:39.326
My kidneys are fine.
I been using the dialysis
money to go gamble.

17:39.359 --> 17:41.728
I've lost everything.
Don't judge me.

17:41.761 --> 17:45.132
Whoa, whoa-- Wait, wait.
What-- What do you mean
everything?

17:45.165 --> 17:48.401
Remember when I told you to
sign the business over to me
in case something bad happened?

17:48.435 --> 17:51.338
Something bad happened.
Mama found on-line Pai Gow.

17:51.371 --> 17:53.573
That business
was gonna be mine.

17:53.606 --> 17:56.309
How could you do this
to the family? How--

17:56.343 --> 17:58.845
How could you lie
right to our faces?

17:58.878 --> 18:01.248
Baby, we got
any orange soda?

18:01.281 --> 18:05.785
- Oh, my God, it's a Negro.
Quick, we're bein' robbed!
- I got him.

18:05.818 --> 18:09.622
- Earl! Grab his feet, Son.
- Let him go, Buzz.

18:09.656 --> 18:12.592
Help me hold him
till the cops get here, Son.

18:12.625 --> 18:15.228
Stop callin' me "Son," okay?
I'm not your son.

18:15.262 --> 18:17.797
I can't do this anymore.

18:17.830 --> 18:20.467
- He's your son.
- What?

18:20.500 --> 18:22.702
I'm your son.

18:22.735 --> 18:24.704
You are?

18:24.737 --> 18:26.906
You Thelma's boy?

18:26.939 --> 18:29.576
[ Earl Narrating ]
Turns out Buzz
had a secret of his own.

18:32.345 --> 18:35.215
Joy was wrong.
Her father didn't hate
black people.

18:35.248 --> 18:37.217
He loved 'em.

18:37.250 --> 18:38.718
[ Giggling ]

18:42.789 --> 18:45.825
- How'd you find me?
- Well, he is your son.

18:45.858 --> 18:48.628
Look at his ears.
He's got white people ears.

18:48.661 --> 18:50.930
My God.
He is not your son.

18:50.963 --> 18:53.500
He's my husband,
you idiot.

18:53.533 --> 18:56.369
- I didn't tell you 'cause
I thought you were racist.
- I'm not racist.

18:56.403 --> 18:59.339
Why'd you flip out
when I wanted to go out with
that black guy in high school?

18:59.372 --> 19:03.676
Because... that
particular black guy
was your half-brother.

19:03.710 --> 19:06.846
- One of 'em.
- You lyin' son of a bitch.

19:06.879 --> 19:09.882
Well, ain't that the pot
callin' the kettle black.

19:09.916 --> 19:13.553
I'm a black pot, am I?
That'd turn you on,
wouldn't it, buster?

19:13.586 --> 19:17.657
You wanna do it
to a black pot?
You wanna dance, Mr. Kettle?

19:17.690 --> 19:20.693
[ Earl Narrating ]
They argued like this
for the rest of the night,

19:20.727 --> 19:23.696
each one of 'em thinking
that the other's secret
was worse than their own.

19:25.498 --> 19:27.567
But eventually,
morning came,

19:27.600 --> 19:30.470
and when the sun came up
and the creatures
started to stir,

19:30.503 --> 19:32.339
well, they had to stop.

19:35.542 --> 19:39.512
* Have a holly jolly Christmas

19:39.546 --> 19:43.350
* It's the best time
of the year *

19:43.383 --> 19:46.986
* I don't know
if there'll be snow *

19:47.019 --> 19:49.289
* But have a cup of cheer

19:49.322 --> 19:52.425
[ Earl Narrating ]
And before you knew it,
the fightin' was over.

19:52.459 --> 19:55.828
Sure, they all had secrets--
big ones.

19:55.862 --> 19:59.299
But the truth is,
the only reason everybody
was keepin' their secrets...

19:59.332 --> 20:02.335
was 'cause they didn't
want to lose each other.

20:02.369 --> 20:05.672
Now that they had
nothin' to hide, they could
just relax and enjoy Christmas.

20:08.941 --> 20:12.379
And that meant Joy
had the best Christmas
she's ever had.

20:12.412 --> 20:14.314
I could cross her
off my list.

20:14.347 --> 20:16.849
* ...kiss her once for me

20:16.883 --> 20:20.820
* Have a holly jolly Christmas

20:20.853 --> 20:23.956
* And in case you didn't hear

20:23.990 --> 20:29.829
* Oh, by golly have
a holly jolly Christmas
this year *

20:36.403 --> 20:39.272
Hey, Earl?
Yeah, Randy?

20:39.306 --> 20:42.342
What's your favorite
Christmas gift
you ever got?

20:42.375 --> 20:45.478
Probably
my Stretch Armstrong
Stretch Monster. You?

20:45.512 --> 20:47.714
Weeble wobbles.

20:49.516 --> 20:51.984
- Earl?
- Yeah?

20:52.018 --> 20:55.555
I was the one who cut open
your Stretch Armstrong
Stretch Monster...

20:55.588 --> 20:57.924
to see what was inside.

20:57.957 --> 20:59.992
I know, Randy.

21:03.530 --> 21:05.798
Merry Christmas.
Merry Christmas.
